.TH man 1 "Jan 5, 2013" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "gadu - git-annex disk usage"
.SH NAME
gadu \- git-annex disk usage
.SH SYNOPSIS
gadu [options] [<path>...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
gadu is a program that determines the sizes of annexed files in a git-annex repository in a manner similar to the du program for normal files.
.SH OPTIONS
 -0, --null            end lines with a null character rather than a newline character
 -B, --block-size      set the block size
 -a, --all             print counts for all files, not just directories
 -b, --bytes           output size in bytes rather than 1024 byte blocks
 -c, --total           print the total of all the command line arguments
 -h, --human-readable  print sizes in human readable format (e.g, 1K 234M 2G)
 -k                    like --block-size=1K
 -m                    like --block-size=1M
 -s, --summarize       display only a total for each argument
 -V, --version         print version
 --help                display a brief help message
.SH SEE ALSO
git-annex(1)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Steve Seltzer
